A
7-year-old boy died this morning after he was hit by a bus at the Claredon and
Birmingham Road intersection in Actonville. Paramedics
found the body of the young boy lying in the middle of the road. The bus
that had struck the boy was parked just a short distance away. The ER24
spokesman, Russel Meiring said paramedics quickly assessed the boy and found that
he had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. “Unfortunately,
nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead. Fortunately, no-one
from the bus sustained any injuries,” he said. Local
authorities were on the scene for further investigations.